inn1.comm: Praveen starts with a ball very wide of off stump and swinging away late. Called a wide.
Praveen trots in and lands this back of a length on leg, and it straightens into the pads. Nudged off the back foot towards square leg. Goes off the pad.
another big wide outside off, Praveen is moving the ball nicely, but the line is a little awry.

that's the line, gentle pace from Praveen angles in towards leg and then curls away late, forcing Edwards into a tentative poke. Outside edge doesn't carry, this is a very slow pitch, and Parthiv dives away to parry it on the bounce and it scoots through to the left of first slip and away for four.
moves this one to the line outside off, not as wide as before, but an easy leave nevertheless.

the deception after setting him up with a series of away swingers, this one holds its line and hits the pad as Edward looks to turn it around to the leg side. That bounces extra and hit him very high, easily missing the stumps.
the outswinger again, Edwards let it go as it starts moving from well outside off.
finishes with a very full ball that angles in, and Edwards digs it out from the crease.
length ball, on a McGrath lengh outside off and holding its line, played cautiously to the leg side.
fuller this time, but not there for the drive. Simmons defends to the off side.
goes wider outside off, and the first touch of away movement for Munaf. Simmons lets it go through.
slightly fuller, closer to the stumps, Simmons is not tempted yet.
he's lived up to the McGrath comparison so far. On a length outside off, Simmons defends after getting confidently across.
maiden from Munaf. Ends with another disciplined ball, back of a length outside off and wafting away gently. Another leave from Simmons.
edgy from Edwards. Praveen again gets that swerve away, and Edwards looks to play, then decides to leave late, but ends up edging it to third man even as he pulls the bat away.

lovely ball, legcutter of sorts, and Edwards does well not to nick it. It came in and nipped away, even as it bounced true, and Simmons' outside edge was just inside the line as he tried to cover for the movement.
this one holds the line, Simmons plays it cautiously to the leg side.
back of a length stock delivery outside off, this is not an easy pitch when the ball is new, and Simmons lets it go to Parthiv.
hint of width this time, Simmons gets half across to it and then chooses to leave again.
quiet start from the Windies, it is not even a whisper. Praveen keeps it a foot outside off and gets it to bend away, and Simmons leaves again.

clanged by Rohit Sharma. Not sure what he's doing at first slip, he's used to being in the covers. Lovely ball from Munaf, gentle curve away as it comes out of the hand and lands outside off, and then not so gentle movement off the seam. Edwards is sucked into a loose drive, and the edge goes at a nice catchable height to Rohit's right. He gets both hands to it and drops it.
Simmons looks to make something happen here, half a step outside the crease and he looks to crack him through the covers, but doesn't place it too well.
not very McGrathesque there. Munaf pushes this well down the leg, and the other Patel doesn't get his gloves to it.
top shot from Simmons, he trots out towards the pitch of the ball, converts a length ball into a half-volley and then launches it over Munaf's head.
nice diving stop from Kohli at point, he moves quickly to the right and dives to his right to keep the steer down to a single.
Edwards tries to chop from the off-stump line, and gets another single away.
good finish from Munaf, whangs it in a little shorter and extracts a extra yard of bounce. Simmons realises it at the last moment and drops the wrists after thinking of cutting.
Praveen keeps it fuller than Munaf, draws the batsman forward into a defensive push.
nicely clipped, though he left it for the very last moment as Praveen got this to hold its line and home in towards the front pad.
back of a length on off stump, Simmons jumps behind the line and defends with a flourish. Very reminiscent of Sherwin Campbell.
again on off stump, Simmons opens the face and he moves into another defensive push.
hmm, risky from Simmons, he shuffles all the way across to off stump and looks to work Praveen around towards midwicket. If he'd closed the face any later, that would have hit the pad.
another good over from Praveen, gets this one to angle in towards the pads from short of a length and Simmons nudges towards midwicket.
not much movement in the last couple of overs, Munaf gets another one to come through straight towards leg stump and it is played to the leg side cautiously.
moves the line to a foot outside off, and again nothing for the drive. Edwards drives into the covers without moving his feet towards the ball.
too straight this time from Munaf, and Edwards works it backward of square leg for a single.
Munaf cuts one in off the seam, and it has Simmons in some strife as he gets the front pad far too much across. No damage done though, he negotiates it after taking the top hand off.
tight single, Simmons reaches out and plays a length ball into the covers and scurries through.
length fare at 84 mph, moving this way and that. This time it comes in off the seam, and Edwards forces it towards midwicket.

horror shot from Simmons, he has combusted with an ugly-looking top-edge that's ended in mid-off's hands. He had decided early that he was advancing down the track, and Praveen had enough time to see him and drop it short. Simmons then threw his hands at an attempted pull, though he was in no position for it. It took the top-edge and looped into Harbhajan's hands.
angles in from slightly wide of the crease, Darren gets forward and drives into the covers.
angles away from Darren, lands on middle and off, and holds its line. He lets it go.
similar ball, Darren flourishes the feet back and across the way that other legend from Trinidad used to, and then leaves.
fuller this time, and wider outside off, Darren Bravo lets it go again.
gets him to play this time, with a full ball on middle and off, and Darren Bravo check-drives into the covers where Dhawan dives to stop.
Munaf keeps bending them in from a foot wide of the stumps, and Edwards works it to the leg side after moving across.
too straight, Edwards easily steps inside the line and whips backward of square for a single.
the disdain. Short and wide from Munaf, enough room for Bravo to play a Lara special. He gets back and across, rides the bounce and smashes the square cut through point.
strong response from Munaf, gets one to swerve sharply away from Bravo. The length was better too, it was not there for the cut, and Bravo just threw his bat at it without moving into line.

and gone. Munaf has nailed Darren Bravo with another nagging ball, short of driving length outside off. Poor shot from Darren Bravo, again he doesn't move forward or back and just throws the bat hard at it. The ball bounds off the outside edge, to Rohit at the lone widish slip and he takes it really well as it flies towards his head. He takes it with the fingers pointing up, even as he falls back.

Ronnie is away, with a spanking shot. Have been watching Munaf for a while now, and his post-wicket balls tend to be loose. Another example here - short and wide outside off, Sarwan stays beside the line and cracks a resounding cut through cover-point.
Edwards again gets the front pad dangerously across the stumps and works a length ball towards midwicket.
tight single taken, late response from Sarwan. Edwards drives hard to mid-off and takes off and the throw goes to the keeper's end. Sarwan makes it.
back of a length from Praveen, and away movement off the seam. Sarwan stays on the crease and shoulders arms.
closer to off stump and fuller too, at 78 mph. Sarwan eases into the defensive check-drive into the covers.
back of a length outside off, and the ball stays low for the first time today. Sarwan lets it go.
short of a length ball angling in from outside off, and Edwards works it off the back foot to midwicket
another one on the pads, Edwards shuffles across and glances it backward of square for one.
better line, around off and middle and still back of a length. Sarwan defends compactly.
defensive again from Sarwan, opens the face and plays him into the covers.
Munaf goes too straight again, Sarwan fends it away off the hips without much conviction, and the ball pops away off the pads, close in on the leg side, allowing a single.
Edwards again motions across the stumps and whips through square leg for a single. Sedate start, at the end of the Mandatory Powerplay.
flat ball to start off, straightens from middle and leg and it is defended.
more air this time and a hint of turn, Edward defends cautiously
tossed up well up on middle stump, and Edward defends again
good start from Mishra, four balls on the right lengths, and Edwards again reaches to the pitch and defends.
flighted on middle and again spinning away from Edwards who defends.
maiden from Mishra. Flighted, almost over-pitched on the pads, but Edwards lets him get away with it, turning it straight to midwicket.
short and wide again from Munaf to Ronnie, this time Sarwan finds point with the cut.
lands this closer to the line of off stump and Sarwan looks to chop despite not having the room. Gets a single towards third man.

nervy single, but Edwards gets away with it. Edwards again moves across the stumps and works Munaf to midwicket where a diving effort is fumbled. The ball is parried to Mishra at mid-on who swoops in and tries to under-arm the stumps at the bowler's end, but the real trouble was at Sarwan's end.
Sarwan stays beside the line to a slower ball at 115 kph outside off and guides it down to third man.
on off stump and holding its line, Edwards stays on the crease and defends down the track.
fullish ball to finish off, on the stumps and Edwards drives it hard but straight to mid-on.
another dot ball for Mishra, this time Sarwan looks to work him against the spin towards midwicket.
flat ball, seemed to skid on towards Sarwan who defended with bat and pad close together as he reached out.
lands this well outside leg and gets it to turn in, Sarwan works it against the spin backward of square. Still no run.
generous flight and ample turn away from Sarwan, who tries to cut but finds point.
nicely played, Sarwan leans into a cover drive and times it well but Raina dives to refuse the single.
aha, he over-steps as he tries to send in a skidder, and Sarwan is troubled a little as he defends from the crease.
Sarwan looks to boom him over the covers, but finds the man sweeping in the deep. Only a single taken.
legcutter outside off, Sarwan walks into a check drive, and pinches a single
on Edwards' pads, and he has looked content to keep nurdling singles with wristy whips through midwicket. Here's another.
outside Sarwan's off stump and he drives into the covers without much timing.
on the pads this time, Sarwan nudges to square leg for an easy single.
short of a length outside off, footwork is an alien concept to Edwards, who stays on the crease and swats it like a fly towards mid-off for a single.
slow legcutter, lands on middle and straightens, but Sarwan is wary to turn the face at the right instant and get a single backward of square leg.
starts with an offbreak outside off, and breaking in. Sarwan works it with the spin to midwicket.
tossed up on off stump, Sarwan reaches to the pitch and plays it back down the track.
he gets him away, working with the spin through midwicket for a single.

dropped by Parthiv, and then by Badri. Harbhajan lands this well outside leg, and Edward nicks the flick onto Parthiv's pad, who fails to hold on. It deflects and flies towards Badri at leg slip, who also can't pouch it.
tossed up on off, Sarwan stays behind the line and defends.
Sarwan looks to work a flighted offbreak from outside off, and ends up playing all over it.
nice delivery this, again a back of driving length legbreak that hits Sarwan's pad after spinning lesser than he anticipated.
this one is too wide outside off, Sarwan lets it go.

nervous times for the Windies. Has Parthiv fluffed a stumping here? Mishra lulls Sarwan out with a classic legbreak, that loops in and goes away. Parthiv fails to collect as Sarwan's back foot comes out for a moment as he over-balances.
top shot, there was less-room there than a studio apartment in Hong Kong, but Sarwan managed to cut it with some power through backward point.
flight this time well outside off, Sarwan leans into a flowing drive and gets it past Raina's diving effort in the covers.
Edwards gets a very full ball outside off, and drives it hard straight to mid-off.
Harbhajan tosses the first ball after drinks on off and Sarwan works it around to midwicket.
hmm, another tight single and Sarwan nudges to midwicket and scoots across. Edwards had to hustle in before the stumps were broken at the striker's end.
short of a length this time, Edwards stays back and works it to midwicket for a single.
worked off the pads to midwicket.
huge appeal from Harbhajan who tosses it up on off and gets Sarwan into a tangle as he looks to flick. Was hitting outside the line by the looks of it.
nice ball to end the over, Harbhajan looks to bring leg slip into play and Sarwan nearly plays into the trap.
googly from Mishra, spinquisition of sorts this for the Windies. Edwards looks to cut and chops an inside edge past the stumps towards fine leg.
and a lovely loopy legbreak to follow it up, Edwards is sucked into a front foot, work off the pads and gets a leading edge that almost carries into the covers.
another legbreak, nice flight, and Edwards is wary of the variations. He's trying to pick him off the pitch.
flighted on the off stump line, and Edward pushes forward nervously to play it back to the bowler.
flatter this time, Edwards middles a straight force but Mishra gets in the way.

poor effort from Harbhajan at midwicket. Edwards has no idea what Mishra is up to. This one was tossed well up in leg stump, and Edwards approaches it as if he is checking if there's a snake under a toppled basket. He plays an awry whip and the leading edge balloons up. Harbhajan runs back, but doesn't move fast enough and can't get his hands to it as it drops over his right shoulder.
defends the first ball back to the bowler.

and Edwards' woes against spin have come to an end. He's scarcely read a ball today from the tweakers. Harbhajan lands the floater short of a length, Edwards leans back and looks to play for the offbreak, and ends up top-edging a pulled whip that lobs up and lands in Kohli's hand at slip. Poor, poor shot.
Samuels gets a big offbreak first up and pushes at it with bat and pad close together as he reaches forward.
Samuels is away, nice curl and turn for Harbhajan, but this time Samuels works him to fine leg.

huge appeal for caught behind, but it is not given. Short ball, extra bounce and turn down the leg side as Sarwan looks to work it to the leg side. Parthiv collects and doesn't appeal immediately, but Harbhajan was vociferous. Not given.
another googly, Samuels cuts it against the break for a single.

direct hit and the third umpire is called into play. Short of a length from Mishra, Sarwan works it off the pads to Harbhajan at mid-on and takes off. Samuels wasn't interested, and Sarwan turned around late. Harbhajan hurled the stumps down at the keeper's end, but Sarwan was in by a foot or so.
short from Mishra, outside off and Sarwan plays that bread and butter cut off his, away for a couple through point.
more air from Mishra, gets Sarwan forward into a defensive push
even more flight this time, and Sarwan gets to the flight carefully and defends.
Mishra pushes this down the leg side, Parthiv fumbles but stops it.
short ball outside off to finish the over.
turning in from outside off, worked with the spin through mid-on for a single.
back of a length this time and drifting down the leg side, Sarwan nudges to the leg side.
this one skids along, not too many revolutions on the ball, and Sarwan defends it from the crease.
tossed further up, Sarwan works him away for a single.
sharp offbreak comes in towards Samuels who is trapped on the pads in front of off. Huge appeal, but it is turned down. Replays say it was missing leg.
tossed up on off and turning away, Sarwan pushes it into the covers.
floats this well up on the stumps and gets it to grip away from Sarwan pushes it into the off side off the outside edge.
short and big turn away from Sars who cuts uppishly through backward point.
fuller length to Samuels and he forces it down the ground for a single.
huge appeal, this is a nice spell from Mishra and he rips another legbreak past the defences to hit Sarwan's pad. Turned down, but was it missing off? Replays say it wasn't.
Sarwan pushes him with the spin for another single.
short of a length and breaking in, Sarwan works it with the spin to midwicket for a single.
fuller to Samuels who leans out to defend with the spin to the mid-on region.
Samuels is playing inside the line, he is concerned about that doosra. Pushed off the outside half into the covers.
he lunges forward again, and this time gets a single into the covers.
Sarwan works a short of length ball with the spin through backward square leg to retain strike.
Mishra slips in another sharp legbreak past Samuels' tentative outside edge. He's not getting forward enough to smother the turn and Mishra is spinning a web around these two now.
draws him forward with another flighted ball and Samuels drives it back to the left of the bowler who dives and saves.
he's tossing them up with authority now, Samuels looks to power it throught he covers but mis-hits it back to the bowler.
and now he slips in another googly, Samuels fishes for it and it shoots in through the defences, but misses the stumps.
tossed up again, every ball has more flight than the previous! Samuels manages to drive this past wide mid-on for one.
Sarwan gets another on middle and leg, and forces it off the inside edge through the square leg area.
back of a length from Harbhajan, Sarwan pushes it from the crease through mid-on.
flighted on off stump from round the wicket, Samuels defends without scoring intent.
angles in towards off this time and straightens it in, Samuels again pats it down the track.
similar ball, Samuels defends once again.
on middle this time, Samuels looks to work it to the leg side, but finds midwicket.
back of a length and straightening into the stumps, Samuels still can't get it away.
tossed up on the stumps, not much turn and it is easily worked through midwicket for a single.
flatter and turning down the leg, nudged backward of square for a single
too short and turning down the leg side, Sarwan pounces on it with a pull shot but finds the fielder.

another poor ball from Yusuf, short and turning well down the leg side. Samuels just had to get bat on that to pick up four, and he did that. Kohli tries to haul it in, and ends up running into the boundary boards.
better line, and length. Samuels pushes forward and across to defend an offbreak coming in.
Yusuf is the fifth bowler and with good reason. Another half-tracker to finish the over and Samuels thumps it through midwicket for four more.
tossed up on the off stump, and Sarwan works it through midwicket for one.
nice shot, Raina again flights it up on off stump and Samuels drives with accomplishment into the deep extra cover region for a couple. The part-timers are doing him a world of good.
fuller and closer to off stump, too close to Samuels for the drive and he defends.
over-pitched on the stumps, and Samuels drives through mid-on for one more.
electric from Tiwary at midwicket, he prances after Sarwan's nudge to deny him the single.
Raina gets one too full and Sarwan just about manages to squeeze it out of play.
flat ball on off stump, worked with the turn to midwicket and this time Raina flies away to intercept and deny the single.
more air this time, Samuels drives against the spin through the covers.
Sarwan jumps out to the pitch and works him with the turn towards midwicket
slides this one down the leg side and it is called a wide.
flat ball on off, and coming in. Sarwan pushes him through mid-on for a single.
Samuels stays back in the crease and forces Yusuf towards long-off
Sarwan pushes a ball turning in towards square leg for one.
flat and quick on off stump, Sarwan stays on the crease and defends.
fuller and allows Sarwan to reach out and drive it towards extra cover for one.
Samuels stays on the backfoot and chops a single towards point
fuller on off stump, Sarwan plays with soft hands into the covers for a single.
Samuels hangs back and chops another single through the point area.
and Sarwan now, cuts a single backward of the point region.
indipper lands on middle and leg, Sarwan pushes it into the covers.
similar ball, hint of width outside off and Sarwan tries to force the cover drive but can't time it.
and a slow legcutter this time, Sarwan picks it off the pitch and defends.
fuller this time, Sarwan drives it with good timing, but can't find the gap.
good effort from Kohli, Sarwan drives it well to the left of the bowler, who tumbles away on his follow through
maiden for Kohli. Short and wide outside off, and Sars mistimes the cut straight to point
Raina tosses this up on the stumps and it is hit right back at him.
short of a length and turning in, Samuels whips straight to midwicket. They have to get these part-timers away.
Windies bring up their 100 at long last. Short of a length outside off and Samuels guides it into the covers for one.
hint of width outside off, and Sarwan cuts it backward of point for one.
flat ball turning into Samuels who works it away to midwicket
Samuels mistimes another cut, as Raina breaks one in from outside off. This is painful progress for the Windies.
back of a length outside off, Sarwan punches off the back foot and finds short cover.
at long last, Sarwan solves the Kohli conundrum. Short ball outside off, and he cuts him through point for one.
Samuels is beaten outside off as he tries to stay back and force a legcutter/
very full from Kohli and Samuels drives fluently to deep cover for one.
nice ball, Kohli gets one to come in sharply and Sarwan gropes for it uncertainly. He chops it on, it misses the stumps and Parthiv can't stop it.
ah, Kohli over-steps with a fullish ball well outside off. Samuels plays it into the covers.
Samuels loves the part-timers especially if they are bowling free-hits at him. He's thundered a length ball over long-on for a big six. Gets under it easy and smashes it.

big appeal for lbw but Sarwan escapes. Fullish on off stump and turning in, Sarwan missed the flick and was hit on the pad. Looked adjacent, but the umpire thought otherwise. Sars was outside the crease, but Parthiv missed a potential stumping. He's having a horror day.
good response from Sars, he jumps out, gets close to the pitch and smites a tossed up ball over the midwicket region for a boundary. Nice hit.
Raina flights it again, this time, Sarwan drives into the covers for a single.
Samuels reaches towards the pitch of a tight offbreak and defends.
shorter length outside off, Samuels stays back in the crease and tries to force it away, but he can't get it away for runs.
starts with a length ball that angles in, and Sarwan works it off the pads through square leg.
back of a length outside off, Samuels seemed to be advancing and Praveen dropped it short and forced him to steer it tamely to point.
this one angles in through the air and finishes on leg. Samuels pushes it down the ground for a single.
Praveen keeps it on that nagging length outside off and Sarwan defends it into the off side.
Praven gets this one to move in gently, cramping Sarwan for room as it does, and he manages to guide it into the point area for one.
variation gone bad, Praveen's attempted legcutter drops short and Samuels redirects it through the gap between midwicket and square leg for an easy four. Well-controlled pull shot that.
starts off with a gentle legcutter, Sarwan guides it off the back foot through point, even as he is squared up.
too full on the pads, Sarwan easily flicks through square leg for a single.
full ball on middle to follow up, Samuels stays on the crease and defends sedately.
subtle legcutter now, lands on leg and jumps up to hit Samuels on the glove. He is taken by surprise as it runs away towards gully.
short ball sliding down the leg side, and it was asking to be bashed through backward square leg. Samuels tries to pull, and miscues it.
full toss on the stumps, Samuels drives it well, but straight to long-off and gets a single.
Praveen gets some gentle away movement again, and Samuels defends off the outside half of the blade into the off side.
Praveen again keeps it short of a length on and outside off, Samuels is waiting for a fuller length, and can't do much with this.
Praveen's a smart cookie. Another one short of a length with no pace on it, around off stump, and Samuels works it without timing towards midwicket.

huge appeal for lbw, but the batsman survives again. Legcutter from Praveen, angles in towards middle and then straightens as Samuels looks to whip and misses. Replays say that would have clipped leg.
Samuels finally gets the single, pushes a length ball down the ground without much comfort.
width outside off to end the over, Sarwan cuts it away through backward point for a single.
another big lbw appeal turned down. Fullish ball, but this one drifted to land on leg. Sarwan tried to swipe through the leg side and nmissed. It was hitting leg stump, but not the whole ball.
closer to leg and middle, Sarwan covers the line and defends.
tossed up again, Sarwan drives down to long-on for a single.
Samuels drives through the covers for a single this time.
Sarwan stays back and glides it off the face into the off side for a single.
Samuels works one off the pads through backward square leg for a single. Time for drinks.

slips the first one well down the leg side and then appeals for a catch behind, as Sars misses the flick. I guess Parthiv was just happy to have collected a ball, and he chose to appeal. Called a wide.
short of a length on middle and straightening, Sarwan taps into the off side for a single.
full ball on middle and leg, Samuels tries to crunch the drive through the off side, but finds cover.
short of a length and angling into the pads, Samuels nudges through square leg for a single.

ohh, deliciously delicate! Sarwan stays on the crease, waiting beside the line as a length ball angles in towards him, and then opens the face of the bat with the most flexible of wrists. The ball purrs away through third man for four. Fifty to Ronnie Sars.

very poor from Munaf, he lands this well outside leg and very full. With fine leg inside the circle. Sarwan cashes in with a neat little glance for four more. Windies are picking up in the batting PP.

what a poor ball to lose a wicket to. Munaf has been concentrating on the channel of complete certainty outside leg stump so far this over. This time Sarwan tries to glance what would have been a wide, and ends up nidking it fine. Parthiv does really well to dive away to his left and pouch it.  Sars c Patel b Patel.
tossed up on the stumps, Samuels pushes it in front of square
tossed up on off stump, Bravo leans out to the pitch and defends.

sloppy from India. Bravo works him with the turn to Raina at midwicket and they take off the for the single. Raina swoops on it and fires in a throw that misses the stumps. Parthiv and Yusuf backing up can't stop it either. Bravo is away with 5.
Samuels was playing for the doosra, but it is an offbreak that hits the pad and pops into the leg side.
Bravo works him into the leg side for another single.
aha, Samuels walks away a metre outside leg and then saunters back in as Harbhajan keeps it flat on leg stump. Samuels pulls hard but finds the man at deep backward square leg.
over-pitched by Munaf and Samuels smashes it right back. Munaf non-chalantly puts a boot out to stop it. On another day, his ankle would have been shattered to smithereens.
another fuller length ball, Samuels leans out to work it to the leg side, but can't get it away.
over-pitched outside off, Samuels thumps it through the covers and Praveen does well to dive and stop. It would have been a sure four if it had got past him.
slower ball at 68 mph, short and wide outside off and cut away without timing.
another slower ball, but Munaf again drops it short. Samuels heaves the pull away to the deep, and Harbhajan at deep midwicket does well to save the boundary.
over-pitched this time, and Samuels indulges in some typical Caribbean flair as he drives with a flourish inside-out. The fielder at extra cover manages to keep it in, but they get two more.
straightens from middle and leg, Bravo defends down the track
on the pads this time, and nudged with the turn to midwicket.
Harbhajan fires it in full on leg stump and Bravo bunts to long-on for a single.
short of a length and turning into the pads, Samuels eases it into the midwicket area.,
pathetic running from Samuels. Full ball on the pads, bravo whips with soft hands and there was two in that all the time. Bravo realised it late, and Samuels never did.
another dot ball to end the over, Harbhajan keeps it flat on middle and leg, and forces him to push it back down the track.
tossed up on off, and Bravo leans out to push it towards cover. More intent please!

here comes the intent! Bravo reaches out to a flighted ball, gets under it and sends it rocketing into the region behind the midwicket fence. Clean swing, and that will make Mishra rethink his length in the end overs.
he produces a googly now outside off, and gets Bravo to cut, and the inside edge scatters towards short fine leg for a single

shot of the innings from Marlon. He has sashayed down the pitch, into a loopy ball on middle and leg and just charmed it over long-on. No violence in that shot, just a nice fluid motion that began with the feet and ended with those smooth hands. Nice way to reach 50.
Mishra wisely keeps it flat, and Samuels pushes it into the off side as he is cramped to cut.
another flat ball on middle and off, Samuels gets it away towards midwicket for a single. End of the Powerplay, and West Indies will be happy with what they got out of it. Eight more overs to go.
flat ball on the pads, worked with the spin through midwicket.
Bravo jumps back, opens up some room and guides an offbreak through backward point for a couple.
Bravo works him with the turn now, single through wide mid-on.

Raina does what he specialises in, producing a huge wicket out of no where. Another wicket goes to an ordinary ball. It was a flat, short, gentle offbreak on middle. Samuels looked to move across and pull it away, but it somehow slipped through off the inside edge, onto his left thing, in between his legs, and clattered the furniture.
flighted on off stump, driven against the turn into the wide mid-off area. Baugh is away.
Bravo pushes a single, working Raina with the turn through mid-on.
short of a length on leg and straightening, forced from the crease down the ground.
slower this time, and very full outside off, Baugh leans out and opens the face to steer it to short third man for a single.
another nagging legcutter on middle and off, played back to the bowler.
Bravo works this one off the pads towards midwicket for a single.
Baugh works him with soft hands to deep midwicket, and a poor throw from Badri allows him to prance back for the second run.
over-pitched on the pads, Baugh works him through wide mid-on for one more.
super shot from Baugh. Tossed up on middle and straightening in for the lbw, Baugh reverses the grip in a flash and slaps it through third man. Lovely, lovely stroke.
tossed well up on off stump, and Baugh pushes through mid-off for one more.
the floater dropped short and it hurries through, Bravo defends and forces it away off the outside half.
horror ball, a foot and a half down the leg side and turning further away. Credit to Parthiv for collecting it.
better line, it is on middle and leg, and Bravo works it to the leg side.

and Harbhajan's got his former Mumbai Indians team-mate. Lovely tossed up delivery on middle stump, and it held it's line. Bravo tried to work it to the leg side, but he wasn't to the pitch of it, and it snapped away past the outside edge even as he over-balanced. Parthiv's day has kept improving, and he collects this nicely and whips the bails off.
slider to end the over, nervous poke from Sammy as he fails to read the lack of turn and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
short ball outside off, Baugh cuts but finds point.
on the pads, Baugh turns it away softly towards midwicket and hares back for a second.
loopy ball on off stump, Baugh drives it well, but straight to cover.
tossed up again, Baugh defends after covering for the turn.
Mishra's spell comes to an end as Baugh drives him down towards long-off and settles for a single.
flat and fierce outside leg, Baugh tries to sweep but can't get bat on it. Rather optimistic lbw appeal, rightly turned down.

third umpire checks on a direct hit. Baugh gets outside the line and drives Harbhajan against the spin through extra cover. Sammy came back for the second and had to put in a big dive, as the throw came in and shattered the stumps. Sammy's bat was in, but did it bounce in the air after hitting the turf? Looks like it came back down in time.

very full outside off, Baugh looks to drive away from the body, but doesn't get it away. Parthiv collects and appeals for a catch, Harbhajan joins in the appeal late. The umpire Peter Nero initially says not out, and then chooses to check with his colleague. And they finally decide to go to the third umpire. Well, well. The bat went close to the turf as Baugh swung. No real evidence that the bat hit the ball, or if it hit the pitch. No noise either, other than that of the ball pitching before he played the shot. Has to be not out. Well, they have spent a real long time checking on this. Has the third umpire nodded off? Green light comes on. Celebrations. Time hasn't stopped on us!
and a leading edge now, Baugh doesn't spot the straighter one and turns the face too early. The leading edge pops up and lands behind Harbhajan as he runs back.
Sammy works Harbhajan with the turn towards short fine leg for one more.

Harbhajan's got an lbw with the last ball of his spell. He's been appealing for them all day! This was a super-fast delivery fired in flat and straight from round the wicket. Did that land inside the mat? No. Poor decision from umpire Nero. Baugh was hustled into the sweep and missed, but once it pitches outside leg, it can't be out.
full and wide outside off, Sammy reaches well out to edge it away into the off side for a single.
full toss on off stump, Rampaul drives into the covers and they belatedly decide to take what was an easy second run. 200 up.
slowish length ball on the pads, Rampaul gets pad as he tries to whip it away, and gets a leg bye.
short and very wide outside off, easy guided carve for Sammy into the covers and this time he comes back for the second.

Praveen's taken Sammy out. You don't get lbws plumber than those. Praveen delivered a low full toss that was headed for the base of middle stump. Sammy got across and tried to work it over to the leg side, and ended up looking like a deer caught in the headlights. Caught palpably in front, and he's walking back now.
Praveen slants one too far down the leg side from round the wicket and it is called a wide.
another slow full toss on off stump, Bishoo pushes into the covers for a single.
full on off stump from round the wicket, Rampaul pushes into the off side
flatter and faster, Rampaul goes back and tries to force it into the off side, but Raina cleans up.
Rampaul gets him away finally, heaving a single towards deep backward square leg.
flat ball on the pads, Bishoo gets a leading edge back towards Raina.
on the pads, Windies have sputtered to a hopeless finish here. Bishoo chips him straight to midwicket.

and gone. Fired in full and on the stumps, Bishoo goes for a reverse-sweep and misses. Another easy lbw call. Or is it? The ball was not entirely inside the mat, but it was still a fair call from the umpire. Hitting off stump.
full ball angling in towards the pads, and Rampaul works it through midwicket for a single.
full ball on middle stump, and Martin plays it with the kind of cautious flourish you expect of a tail-ender. Single to mid-on.
very full on Rampaul's pads, and flicked through midwicket for one more.
legcutter at 102 kph, Martin doesn't look like he can pick it, and misses it by a long way as it bounces twice on the way to Parthiv.
even slower, short ball that comes a year after Martin played the pull, and it pops away for a single.

Praveen finishes with a ball too slow even for slower balls. Rampaul waited and waited, and still ended up slugging it too early and hence too high, straight back. Dhawan at widish long-on did well to cover a lot of ground to his right and get there, but ended up spilling it. West Indies finish with a four.

inn2.comm: short of a good length on leg stump, tries to whip it square, is struck high on the pads and they get a leg-bye
slightly short on leg stump and nipping down, Dhawan tries to close the face on that one and work it square, is struck on the pads, stifled appeal turned down
short and wide and Dhawan tries to slash that through point, misses, Gavaskar calls him a great "practicer" of that shot
quick single, short of a good length on middle, dropped into the off side, Parthiv calls and makes it comfortably
nicely timed, slightly short on leg stump, Parthiv gets across and clips it past square leg for a couple of runs
back of a length but doesn't quite rise up, nips away and Parthiv lets it be
shortish on leg stump, doesn't turn much, played straight to square leg
held it back once again, gets back and whips it to square leg
shortish again, rocks back and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
consistently short this over, on leg stump and it's worked away to deep square leg
flat and fuller on leg stump, tries to clip it square once again, gets an inside edge onto his pads
back of a length outside off, Parthiv runs that down towards third man for a single
short of a good length on leg stump, not connecting too well is Dhawan, gets back to whip it again, is struck on the thighs
nicely timed, short of a good length, stands tall and punches it between the covers for a couple of runs
Dhawan isn't too comfortable out there, Rampaul pushes it on a good length and Dhawan tried to loosely push that through the line, got an inside edge onto his thighs and just wide of leg stump
lovey drive, Rampaul bowled it on a length outside off and Dhawan caressed it between extra cover and mid-off, nice timing and it sped away
a punch this time, off the front foot, landed on a good length and he picked out the gap between cover and point this time, getting into his groove now
Three fours in a row, short ball again on leg stump, Martin's done that several times in the seven balls he's bowled, smashed over square leg
pushed it through on the pads, a touch fuller, tries to turn the face, struck on the pads
gets across to work it into the leg side again, pitched outside leg and caught him on the pads once again
a change of line, on the off stump this time, drew Dhawan forward, defended towards extra cover
punched off the back foot wide of mid-on for a quick single, Sarwan scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Dhawan is comfortably in
nurdles it past midwicket for a single to keep strike
fullish on the off, pushed straight towards cover
short of a good length outside off, Parthiv hung his bat loosely at that one, got an inside edge just wide of the keeper on the bounce, the ball kept a little low there
a little more effort in that delivery, shortish outside off, Parthiv stands tall and knocks it in front of point
oversteps, good length on the off, pushed firmly to mid-off, a freehit coming up, overstepped big time
doesn't spare it, short ball on middle and Parthiv got into position early ti dispatch it over square leg for a boundary, a solid start for the Indians here
he likes that shot but there is cover, short and it's slashed on the bounce to point, the ball spun away off the turf but Bravo had it well covered
good length on the off, pushes it on the up straight to mid-off
tighter line from Martin this time, shortish still but on middle and off, defended into the leg side

run-out, excellent fielding from Dwayne Bravo at mid-on, was pushed wide of him and Parthiv responded to Dhawan's call, Bravo was running to his wrong side, he collected and returned a powerful throw to Baugh at the striker's end, the keeper knocked off the bails to find Parthiv well short
pushed into the off side
gets forward and defends on the pitch
drops it back in front of the bowler
slightly short on the off, punched wide of cover for a single to open his account
played it down to third man for a single
offering him width, giving Dhawan a chance to free his arms, chops it hard wide of point, a dive in the deep and the fielder has hauled it back in just about, three more
lands on a good length on the off, driven with a full face to mid-off
bowled it full on the off, gets a thick inside edge as he tries to drive it straight back, goes towards mid-on
chasing a wide one and Kohli will be livid with that, short and he went for the cut, got a thin edge and Baugh made no mistake, a loose shot and he's paid the price
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and defends it cautiously back to the bowler
slightly short on middle and leg, turned away past square leg for a single
floating it on the off, doesn't toss it up an awful lot does Martin, pushed back wide of the bowler
held it back just a little outside off, Badri covered it well, defending it to point
pushed it through quicker did Martin, surprised Badri who was late to play it and got a thick outside edge, past the diving slip, for three
shortish on middle, rocks onto the back foot to play it to midwicket
a long hop but there is protection in the deep, it's pulled straight to deep midwicket for a single
beaten, drawing him into playing a drive, Dhawan went at that on the up, it nipped away just to beat the outside edge
back of a length on middle, Dhawan gets across and defends it well, getting behind it nicely to play it to mid-off
shortish outside off, chops it behind point towards third man for a single
Badri waits for that one to come onto him and opens the face to guide that to third man for a single
drops it short on middle, gets back and drops it wide of cover for an easy single
nicely done by Badri, there was some width, he cashed in by rocking forward and square-driving that between cover and point, Martin gives chase and dives but can't quite drag it back in
on the leg stump, defended off the front foot in front of th ebowler
bowled it fuller, comes down the track and plays it back to the bowler who shows good reflexes, scoring a direct hit at the striker's end
worked away past square leg for a single
defended off the front foot in front of point, enough time available to squeeze a single
sliding it towards middle and leg, comes down the track and pushes it to midwicket
fuller on middle, gets to the pitch and drops it dead
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
fuller just outside off, gets forward and punches it to cover
quick single, Rampaul fumbled at mid-off, pushed just wide of him and Dhawan called for a single
shortish on middle, Badri's doing it nicely here, turns it away behind square leg for a single
tries to push that through the line towards mid-off, gets a thick outside edge, wide of the diving point, for a single
short of a good length on leg, turned away down to fine leg for a single to keep strike
bowling it flat just outside off, Badri waits for it to turn away and defends it to point
slightly short on the off, punched straight back to the bowler
provides some width, it turns away further, Badri makes room and cuts it through point for a couple of runs

confusion as Badri knocks that wide of Edwards at point, runs through and is sent back after reaching halfway point, Edwards didn't gather that all too cleanly, had he done so and returned the throw in time, Badri would have been in trouble
a really wide one and Badri chased it, could only play it to cover
gets on the back foot and punches it to cover
defended calmly towards extra cover, took a couple of steps down the pitch to that goodish length delivery
width this time and Dhawan cracks that towards point, Edwards does well diving to his left and preventing at least a couple of runs
steals a quick one this time, defends it wide of mid-on off the back foot and races through
short of a good length just wide of off, chopped down to third man just at the last moment for a single
slower one this time, bowled it full on middle and off, driven straight to mid-off
beaten, good bounce for Sammy there, Dhawan tried to open the face just as he was offered some width but it raced past the outside edge
gets forward to that flattish delivery and drops it into the off side
tossed up this time, Badri waited for it to turn away and defended it to point
slightly short on the off, rocks back and knocks it into the off side
stretches forward and taps it towards point
He gave that some rip, spat away from leg stump towards off and caught Badri by surprise, he played that well, taking his bottom-hand off and fending it away behind the keeper
maiden, gets forward and plays it down cautiously into the off side, well done Bishoo
short of a good length, punched it past extra cover into the deep for a single
gets forward and taps that towards mid-on, kept a little low, turned the face a little there
targeting off stump, gets across and works it away to midwicket
full and he senses a chance, gets to the pitch and drives but drives it straight to Edwards at extra cover
tight line, on middle and leg, Badri plays that off the back foot, defended to midwicket
shortish on the off, Badri's been kept quiet in the last couple of overs, 11th dot ball in a row for him, defended to point
gets on the back foot and tickles it towards square leg
Badrinath breaks through, opting to sweep, gets a couple wide of long-leg, played pretty fine

Bishoo breaks through this time, pushed that one quick, landed short on the off and skidded past Badri, he tried to chop that to point, got a faint under-edge and Baugh took it well, India in a bit of trouble now
stifled appeal for lbw, struck on the pads, slid on the pads, Rohit tried to play that straight, got an inside edge onto the pads
beaten, flighted on the off and turns away just as Rohit gets forward to defend

inexplicable from Rohit, was fortunate to get away with that, flighted outside off and turned away, Rohit went after that one, trying to clear mid-off, he managed to do that but didn't really get hold, got plenty of elevation on that one and is lucky to still be out there
Dhawan gets another single, he's not had much strike, punched past cover for a single
nips back in to beat the outside edge, Rohit wasn't expecting the movement, tried to open the face and was beaten
bowled it full on middle, gets forward and chips it towards mid-on
slower one that cuts back in, Rohit opened the face there, getting it wide of Baugh who fumbles to allow them to steal a single
lands on a length outside off, rocks forward and drives it straight to extra cover
short ball down the leg side, Dhawan helps it down to fine leg for a single to keep strike
floated it on middle, fullish, played back to the bowler
bowled it full outside off, driven wide of mid-off to steal a quick single
waited for it to turn away did Rohit and just tapped it behind point for a single, nicely done this time
was the googly from Bishoo, dropped it short on leg stump, Dhawan picked it, rocked back and pulled it wide of deep square leg for a couple
slightly short on middle, gets on the back foot and turns it behind square leg for one more
shortish on the off, moves away to cut it straight to point
fullish on the off stump, gets forward and drives it wide of long-off for a single
shortish outside off, is late to play that, tried to open the face to run it third man but missed
Rohit, what's he trying to do? Counter-attack, but it isn't quite going well, swung that from outside off to deep midwicket, didn't get hold of it
slower ball bowled full on middle, dug out into the leg side towards midwicket
short and wide, mistimes an attempted cut towards cover
well fielded at cover point, cracked hard on the up from Dhawan but wasn't able to pierce the field on the off side
flighted on middle, gets forward and works it wide of midwicket for a single
fetches that flat delivery from outside off and sweeps it to deep square leg for a single
slowed it up and gave it some air, Rohit played that well, waiting for it to come on and tapping it into the off side
comes down the track to get to the pitch this time and drives it wide of midwicket for a single
tossed up on the off, got to the pitch while making a bit of room simultaneously, drove it straight to extra cover
saw him come down and held back the length, Dhawan adjusted well, getting behind it and playing it into the off side
goodish length on middle and leg, gets across to drive it past midwicket for a single
kept low there, cut away, shortish outside of, Dhawan slashed at it but was beaten by the low bounce
a touch fuller, freed his arms there to crack it through the off side but mistimed it completely
gets across, it's bowled short outside off from round the wicket, slapped straight to mid-on
back to over the wicket, straying on the pads, whipped past square leg for a single
placed it well, was a touch too straight from Sammy, turned away through square leg for a couple of runs
shortish on the off, comes down the track and punches it to extra cover
Dhawan's appearing to be getting a little impatient, was short outside off and he dragged it to midwicket
comes down the track, Bishoo alters his length, he can only knock it away with his pads
short ball down the leg side, can't get it past short fine, a bit of frustration, the pressure grows
plays the reverse-sweep which doesn;t quite come off but he gets a single wide of cover
short on the off, Rohit stands tall and slaps it to long-on for a single
starts with a slower one bowled short outside off, drops it behind point for a single
struck firmly, bowled on a lenght and Dhawan cracks it hard past extra cover, Simmons gets to it and returns a slightly wayward throw which helps them complete the second easily
Dhawan steps up, the slower one but in the slot outside off, Dhawan sensed a chance and picked it beautifully, thwacking it over deep midwicket for a flat six
he's hitting it well this over, creamed through the off side in the deep for a single
straying on the pads, Rohit fails to get bat on that one as he tries to clip it square, they steal a leg-bye
shortish on the off, chops it towards point
Bishoo drops that slightly short on the off, punched towards deep cover for a single
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot and turns it wide of midwicket for one more
slowed it up and gave it some air, turning away a hint, Rohit waits for the turn and defends into the off side

appeal for lbw, skidded through with a bit of turn, looked really close, landed on middle and leg and straightened, looked out as it clipped the pad before making contact with the bat, Ian Gould gave it runs but that hit pad first
gets back and knocks it down into the leg side, good over from Bishoo, should have had Rohit there
the offcutter, the slower one, Rohit reads it well and defends it in front of the bowler
pitched up and it's driven past Bravo to long-on for a single
full outside off, driven hard but straight to deep extra cover for a single
nicely done, gets to the pitch and just eases it to long-off for a single
Dhawan's doing well, finds the gap this time and everyone's up in the Indian dressing room, short and wide and he latches onto it, smacking it hard past point
pushed back, was on a good length
flighted on middle, a low full toss, pushed back to the bowler
on a length on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
tossed up on the off, gets across and drives it to midwicket

now Dhawan's lost it, he'd worked hard to get to his half-century and he's thrown it away with that slog-sweep, was tossed up outside off and he sent it straight into the palms of deep midwicket, this is a tight one
gets forward and defends it into the leg side
bowled it full outside off, drilled hard past extra cover into the deep for a couple of runs
starts with a slower one to Raina, bowled full on middle, defended to midwicket
good length on the off, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
chases a wide one, full and wide and it's driven straight to extra cover
slower one bowled short on the off, pushed past midwicket for a single
full on middle, a slower one making him reach forward, played back to the bowler
turned away past square leg for a single
tossed up on the off, driven hard but straight back to Martin
bowled it flat this time, pushed through the line past the diving Martin for a single
floated it on the off, presents the full face while playing it back
gets forward and drives it straight to midwicket
quicker through the air, gets forward and defends with bat close to pad
slightly short outside off, played wide of point for a single
four to start off his new spell, the slower one misdirected on the pads and Raina slyly tickles it past the keeper to beat the man at fine leg
shortish on leg stump, easily played past square leg for a single
cut away, short ball outside off, point got a hand to it, just the single in the deep
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot to point
shortish again, Raina moves back to that one and taps it towards point
defended solidly back to the bowler, tighter line this time, on middle, plays it back
pushes that down the ground to long-off for a single
shortish on middle, gets back and turns it to square leg for a single
pushed that wide of extra cover for one more
pitched up outside off, driven straight to extra cover
flighted on middle, driven hard towards long-on to keep the strike
lands on a good length outside off, eased towards deep point off the front foot
slower one bowled full on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
slower one again, on the pads this time, tickled towards short fine leg
back of a length on the off, punched towards long-off for a single
short on the off, gets on the back foot and turns it past midwicket for a single
slower one bowled full on the off, driven down to long-off for a single
poor start to a new spell, short down the leg side, a gift for Raina who helps it down the fine-leg boundary after getting it past short fine
smartly done by Raina, short of a good length outside off, opens the face to play it behind point for a couple more, waited for it to turn in
ooh, leading edge, tried to play it behind square but turned the face too early there, fell just short of Kirk Edwards at midwicket
dropped into the off side for a quick single, raced off as he played it in front of point
shortish on middle, gets back and knocks it wide of midwicket for a single
short, waits for it to turn in and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single
whips it through square leg
full on the off, dug out in front of cover
short of a good length on the off, punched past cover into the deep for a single
slower one bowled short, stands tall to crack it towards deep cover for one more
low full toss on leg stump, it's pushed wide of long-on for a single, thinks of a second but it isn't there
low full toss outside off, eased towards deep cover to retain the strike
rips that short on the off, played gently past point for a single
shortish outside off, turning in, Raina tries to open the face there but can't make contact
shortish on middle and leg, gets back to play it towards midwicket
driven through for a single to long-off
slightly short on the off, cut towards point, no run there and it's time for drinks
pitched up on the off stump and Raina helps himself to a couple with a drive wide of extra cover

a couple more, this is good going from Raina, full and slow on the pads, pushed firmly past midwicket for a couple more, a good throw from the deep and Sammy takes off the bails but Rohit makes it back safely
good length outside off, square-drives it past point into the deep for a single
Rohit steps out and clears the ropes, was the slower one and he charged out to take it from a a length and dispatch it over the extra cover boundary, takes India past 150, it was his first boundary
good length on the off, driven down to long-on for a single
well fielded by Martin at point, was a slower one bowled short and cut hard but Martin dived to his right to prevent at least a couple of runs
beaten, Bishoo gave that some air and got some turn, Rohit moved away to play the cut but failed to make contact as it kept a little low
quicker through the air, short outside off and it's cut behind point for a couple of runs, brings up the 50-stand
It's slipping away from West Indies here, short outside off and Rohit gets into position early, waited for it to turn away and pulled it over midwicket for a boundary
makes room to chop that towards point
turns away again, shortish, taps it towards cover
driven off the front foot towards extra cover, ends Bishoo's spell
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and taps it towards midwicket
short of a good length outside off, cuts it wide of deep point for a couple more, runs flowing freely here
slower one bowled on a good length, pushed towards point
India pressing home the advantage, slower one bowled full outside off and Raina slices that over point for four more, didn't evade the point fielder by much but it fetches four
punched towards long-off for a single
slower one, reaches forward and drives it to long-on for a single
short of a good length on the off, drops it down towards point
short of a good length outside off, cut straight to point, Rohit will feel he missed out there
runs it down to third man for a single
round the wicket, angling in towards middle, whipped past square leg for a single
good length, comes down the track to clear extra cover again but mistimes it instead to mid-off
a touch too wide outside off as Rohit lets it go, the umpire calls it
sweetly timed on the up towards deep cover for a single
shortish, punched straight towards extra cover
makes room and thwacks it hard past the covers for a boundary to raise a half-century, the field was up and he backed himself to pierce it
turned away into the leg side for a single
Raina tries to sweep that hard but is struck on the pads, pitched outside leg
gets it right this time, strays down the leg side and it's swept hard down to the fine-leg boundary, the fielder was up inside the circle
full on middle, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
angles in from round the wicket, Raina tries to push that through the line but ends up getting a thick outside edge towards short third man, played inside the line to that one
slower one but aiming for the blockhole, dug out back to the bowler
short one down the leg side, Raina fails to make contact but earns a wide
low full toss, driven wide of a diving midwicket for a couple of runs
full on middle, driven all along the ground to a widish long-on for a single
appeal for lbw, got across a little to drive it through midwicket, missed and was struck on the pads but that would have missed leg

Raina has holed out with the job incomplete, was in the slot, tossed up on the off stump but he slog-swept it straight to long-on when in fact he would have wanted to clear deep midwicket, straight to Simmons, a small for the Windies, you think?
pushed it through quicker, held its line, didn't turn, Yusuf played inside the line to that one and was beaten
fires it full down the leg side this time and it's called a wide
full toss on middle, punched down the ground to long-on for a single
misfield at extra cover from Sammy, a full toss it was, punched straight to him and he lets it through to allow them a couple
angling it on the pads, clipped towards wide long-on for a single

dropped, Martin clangs it, full toss and it's driven back gently to the bowler, Martin moved to his right and seemed to have it covered but made it an utter mess of it, big moment in the game. He's distraught, he's fielded well this game but that must hurt
Rohit, meanwhile, cashes in at the other end, full outside off from Rampaul and it's square-driven beautifully past point for a boundary
in the blockhole outside off, dug out toward short third man
two more, low full toss while aiming for the yorker, flicked through square leg for a couple more
a couple more, low full toss again and Rohit helps that past square leg for another brace
Rohit is tiring now, pushed down the ground to long-on and appears in a bit of difficulty at the other end, is it cramps? We don't know yet
bowled full on the off, Yusuf gets that past square leg for a single to keep strike
slightly short on the off, defended into the off side for a single
full outside off and Rohit wants to smash the daylights out of that one but misses and instead it is Baugh who gets hit
slower one bowled short on the off, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
good length on the off, defended towards cover, Yusuf wants the single but Rohit sends him back
length ball and Yusuf gives it the treatment, hammers it hard over the bowler's head for a flat six
short of a good length, taps it towards cover, no single on offer there
short ball outside off, it's guided down to third man for a single
goodish length on the off, defended towards cover
short and wide, tries to slash that past point, makes no contact
gets on the back foot and knocks it down into the leg side for a single
eased off the front foot wide of extra cover for a single

excellent catch from Rampaul, does what Martin failed to do and this was a far more difficult chance, pitched on a length and Yusuf drives it back hard but Rampaul stays alert and pouches it well on his follow through, good stuff
shortish on leg stump, turned away past square leg for a single
